text.tspan: 1. Copy&Paste the shapes below to create new figures, the colours define the commodities
2. In the legend keep only commoditiy that are appering in the figure
3. The system boundary shape and arrows (not the thick one for transport) can be used to represent other entities (e.g. model regions)
4. The different component shapes should be filled in the colour of the respective commodity
5. Try not to change fonts, but feel free to add new colours for new commodities, if missing (while avoiding greys and black)
6. Make all text in bold except commodities names
7. Adjust the legend to only contain elements appearing in your drawing area
8. Adjust the background shape behind your figure keeping about one centimeter from drawing elements on every side
9. Delete all other template elements and save the file (it should automatically be a .svg file) for the documentation
